## alwaysApply: true

# Backend Architecture Rules

## Module Structure

All modules must follow the exact same folder and file structure.

Example:

```txt
user/
├── dto/
│   ├── create-user.dto.ts
│   ├── update-user.dto.ts
│   └── query-user.dto.ts
├── guards/
│   ├── jwt-auth.guard.ts
│   ├── roles.guard.ts
├── helpers/
│   ├── helper.ts
│   └── transform.helper.ts
├── repository/
│   └── user.repository.ts
├── strategy/
│   └── jwt.strategy.ts
├── swagger/
│   └── user.swagger.ts
├── types/
│   └── user.types.ts
├── user.controller.ts
├── user.db.service.ts
├── user.service.ts
├── user.module.ts
└── guest-user-conversion.service.ts
```

Every module must follow the same pattern.

Examples:

```txt
auth/
product/
category/
order/
payment/
notification/
wishlist/
cart/
review/
```

Never invent custom structures per module.

**Repository folder is optional.** If `<module>.db.service.ts` contains Prisma queries directly (no caching/coordination layer), do not add a pass-through `repository/` file. Follow `auth/auth.db.service.ts` as the reference.

